MMT Remarks: Measured off of U/S side of Wapiti bridge. Construction crew had U/S lane shut down for engineering work and they allowed us limited time on the bridge to conduct measurement. Static clothesline set-up approximately 20m U/S of bridge. RiverRay then tethered to that and maneuvered with second line from bridge. Knot at RB prevented getting any closer to that bank and therefore produces an edge greater than 5% of total Q (average of 13%). Limited time available on bridge also prevented a total exposure time of 720 seconds (540 seconds obtained). First CC passed and used. Typical Heading Error: < 0.418°. Vector Addition Of Single And Double Cycle Errors: 0.574°. °Three MBTs conducted. First two aborted due to communication issues. Likely due to extreme distance between computer and instrument.
